March 13,2020.

February 20 of the lunar calendar.

Day fifty-one of the siege of Wuhan.

The 50th day of the closing of the gate of Heaven.

Stocks in the U.S. suffered their third lock-out yesterday -- first in 1997 and then on Monday. I thought it was black Monday, but it's black Monday. I've never seen anything like it in my 89 years of life, said Buffett. "The last time I had a fuse was on March 9,2020. I remember that day as if it was just a few days ago, " said a netizen who has seen the world. Jokes aside, the two meltdowns and global economic crisis caused by the Black Swan may be just the beginning of the real downturn, as the bubble created by the Sichuan Emperor's bluster is turned back into a grey Rhino.

Recall Wang Xing's poignant line in Fanfou in early 2019: "2019 may be the worst year of the past decade, but it's the best year of the next decade. " True. Gone are the days when pigs flew in the wind and made money on their backs. Winter is coming, and only those who are better adapted to the currents and to life after death can survive, as if they were more powerful, a necessary part of human evolution.
